UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Mariza A. LAMELA, a.k.a. Maritza, Defendant-Appellant. No. 08-16377

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Sept. 30, 2009. Kathleen M. Salyer, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Miami, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Mariza A. Lamela, Tallahassee, FL, pro se. *499Before CARNES, WILSON and ANDERSON, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

Monique Broehu, appointed counsel for Mariza Lamela in this direct criminal appeal, has moved to withdraw from further representation of the appellant and filed a brief pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Our independent review of the entire record reveals that counsel’s assessment of the relative merit of the appeal is correct. Because independent examination of the entire record reveals no arguable issues of merit, counsel’s motion to withdraw is GRANTED, and Lamela’s conviction and sentence are AFFIRMED.
